race.comment: Things don't get any easier with a competitive 1514m race with not much separating a number of runners. VAAFEE (3) might find things tough from the wide gate but made progress last time out, finishing 3.5 lengths from the winner in third at the end of 1500m at this track. His best figures measure up. SUNSET BEAUTY (8) finished fifth last time out over 1415m at Sale, beaten 3 lengths. Her previous runs were good and she looks a key player. HEY BELLA (9) finished second last start at the first run back from a spell over 1454m at Kyneton, beaten 1.3 lengths. Likely improver with that run under the belt and gets in nicely after the 2kg claim for a rider who has proven an asset at these sort of meetings. DUBAI FOUNTAIN (10) ran a better race last start, finishing 1.3 lengths away in fourth over 1400m at Holbrook. This a step up, but at peak fitness now, also gets a claim and draws well. VERY GRATEFUL (7) is fitter now and draws much more favourably than some other key players.
